   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2020 grant-support for youth training in skills</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Youth Into Employment Project is implemented by Build It International Zambia (BIIZ) an NGO working to provide support to commuities by providing good quality infrastructure for for health and education.  They use a model which trains youth in construction skills so that they can sustain themselves.  The YEW project is implemented at the BIIZ Centre of Excellence in Chibombo, Central Province which id dedicated to providing high quality construction skills to vulnerable girls and boys based on using  entry eligibility  the poverty probability index  a poverty measurement tool.  To date BIIZ has trained 41 girls and 120 boys.</narrative>
  </description>
